# English Comprehension â€“ Set 4 (New Category)

This set contains short reading passages followed by questions to test comprehension skills.

---

## **Passage 1:**

Technology has transformed the way businesses operate. With automation, companies can complete tasks faster and with fewer errors. However, the rise of automation also demands employees to upgrade their skills regularly. Continuous learning has become essential to remain relevant in the fast-changing digital world.

### **Questions:**

1. What has technology changed according to the passage?
2. Why is continuous learning important?
3. What is one benefit of automation mentioned in the passage?

---

## **Passage 2:**

Healthy communication in a team encourages collaboration and reduces misunderstandings. When team members share ideas openly, projects move forward smoothly. Listening actively is just as important as speaking clearly.

### **Questions:**

4. What improves when communication is healthy?
5. What is equally important to speaking clearly?
6. What happens when ideas are shared openly?

---

## **Passage 3:**

Many companies today focus on sustainability. They aim to reduce waste, save energy, and promote eco-friendly practices. Such efforts not only help the environment but also build a positive brand image.

### **Questions:**

7. What are companies focusing on?
8. What are two eco-friendly actions mentioned?
9. How does sustainability help companies besides helping the environment?

---

## **Passage 4:**

Time management is a crucial skill for students and professionals alike. Those who plan their schedule effectively can complete tasks on time and reduce stress. Procrastination, on the other hand, leads to rushed work and lower quality output.

### **Questions:**

10. Why is time management important?
11. What is one negative effect of procrastination?
12. What benefits come from planning a schedule effectively?
